<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<materialsCitation collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen hereby designated as 
<typeStatus box="[550,653,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male, labeled “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sol. Gal." authorityName="Sol. Gal." box="[869,1201,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="virens" variety="distinctus">
<emphasis box="[869,936,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">virens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[989,1096,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">distinctus</emphasis>
Sol. Gal.
</taxonomicName>
merid. D.”, “Solier”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus box="[463,578,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[615,991,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis box="[615,834,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Anisodactlus virens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[841,991,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName box="[1106,1224,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
Concerning this species 
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[473,634,907,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
stated that: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
Il se trouve assez communément dans le midi de la 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1432,907,932]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">France</collectingCountry>
, et il m’a été envoyé par M. Solier.
</emphasis>
Lately, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[619,779,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean (1831)</bibRefCitation>
briefly described a new 
<taxonomicName box="[1054,1214,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" rank="variety" variety="named">variety named</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1220,1327,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinctus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1327,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">distinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Solier 
<emphasis box="[151,652,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">don’t la coleur est presque entièrement noire.</emphasis>
This name is nowadays considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017 a)" baseAuthorityName="Kataev &amp; Wrase" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="virens" subSpecies="virens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Anisodactylus virens virens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[234,510,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="1854" refId="ref11592" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 a) Subtribe Anisodactylina Lacordaire, 1854. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 503 - 509." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. For this reason, the specimen has been designed as 
<typeStatus box="[1111,1217,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It is dorsally darkcoloured; there are other beetles in the collection (possibly 
<typeStatus box="[824,988,1051,1078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
) with various degrees of green metallic lustre. Variation in dorsal colouration is common in carabids living in salty places. Its characteristics match those of the original description and the current concept of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[199,298,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis box="[199,298,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently included in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Tschitscherine, 1898" authorityName="Tschitscherine" authorityYear="1898" box="[728,1107,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hexatrichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[728,865,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Hexatrichus</emphasis>
Tschitschérine, 1898
</taxonomicName>
, that is characterized by a labrum with many setae at each side, the trifid internal spur of protibia and sexual differences in the anterior leg. The subgenus includes two species which are very similar but can be distinguished by the shape of pronotum and median lobe of aedeagus (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeannel, R." box="[410,567,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
, p. 604).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[199,300,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis box="[199,300,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is polytypic; the nominal subspecies occupies South 
<collectingCountry box="[923,1002,1303,1329]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">France</collectingCountry>
, North 
<collectingCountry box="[1092,1143,1303,1329]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Italy</collectingCountry>
and the Iberian Peninsula whereas the subspecies 
<taxonomicName authority="Dejean, 1831" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" box="[457,834,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="virens" subSpecies="winthemi">
<emphasis box="[457,672,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens winthemi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[682,834,1339,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits 
<collectingCountry box="[943,1013,1339,1365]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, Sicily, NW Afrique, Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Wrase, D. W." box="[159,304,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="889 - 899" refId="ref12584" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2009) On the identity of Amblystomus levantinus Reitter, 1893, and remarks on A. metallescens (Dejean, 1829) (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini, Amblystomina). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 41, 889 - 899." type="journal article" year="2009">Wrase, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and Madeira. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bedel, L." box="[475,623,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="308 - 309" refId="ref10276" refString="Bedel, L. (1898) Note sur l'Anisodactylus winthemi Dej. (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1897, 308 - 309. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1897.22129" type="journal article" year="1898">Bedel (1898)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Antoine, M." box="[677,850,1374,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described the characteristics of this last subspecies; both authors noted that dorsal colouration is variable, and in 
<collectingCountry box="[841,925,1411,1437]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1055,1411,1437]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Maroc</collectingCountry>
is more greenish. These observations are interesting as this subspecies was established according to its dark (almost black) dorsal colouration and geographic origin (
<collectingCountry box="[365,438,1483,1509]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Egypt</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
